    <style type="text/css">
    
    div {
		background:green;
		font-size:130%;     
    }
    
    .redbox {
		background-color:red;    
    }
    
    .bluebox {
		background-color:blue; 
		height:100px;   
    }
    
    .bold {
		font-weight:bold;    
    }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<p> Here we will learn about div. Div is logical separation of a web page. So we can divide a web page in various division by
 putting div tag. It will create several rectangular division of pages. Lets see some example to understand the idea better way. </p>
 
 Syntax : <br />
 <u> simple div</u><br />
 &ltdiv><br />
 content....<br />
 &lt/div><br /></br />
 
 <u> div with style information </u><br />
 
 &ltdiv class="normal_class"><br />
 content....<br />
 &lt/div><br /></br />

Note : Here class is a normal class what we declared in previous section<br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbspDiv are declared in the head part<br />
<br />
Example <br />

&nbsp&nbsp&lthtml><br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&lthead><br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&ltstyle type="text/css"><br /><br />
    
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp    div {<br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp		background:green;<br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp		font-size:130%;     <br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp    }<br /><br />
    
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp    .redbox {<br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp		background-color:red;<br />    
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp    }<br /><br />
    
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp    .bluebox {<br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp    background-color:blue;<br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp    height:100px;<br />    
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp    }<br /><br />

&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp.bold {<br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp		font-weight:bold;<br />    
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp    }<br /><br />
    
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&lt/style><br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&lt/head><br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&ltbody><br /><br />

&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&lt div><br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp This is a default div, if no class attached then this div will trigger<br /> 
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&lt/div><br /><br />

&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&lt div class="redbox"><br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp This a div with redbox style class<br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&lt/div><br /><br />

&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&lt div class="bluebox bold"><br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp This a div with bluebox style class<br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&lt/div><br /><br />


&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&lt/body><br />
&nbsp&nbsp&lt/html><br /><br />

output : <br />

	<div>
		This is a default div, if no class attached then this div will trigger<br /> 
	</div><br />

	<div class="redbox">
		This a div with bluebox style class<br />
	</div><br />
	
	<div class="bluebox bold">
		This a div with bluebox style class<br />
	</div><br /><br />

